==Discography==\n{{main|Crosby, Stills, Nash & Young discography}}\n''For individual discographies, see entries on [[David Crosby#Discography|David Crosby]], [[Stephen Stills#Discography|Stephen Stills]], [[Graham Nash#Discography|Graham Nash]], and [[Neil Young discography and filmography|Neil Young]]. See also [[Crosby & Nash#Discography|Crosby & Nash]] and [[Long May You Run|Stills-Young Band]] for duo discographies.''\n\n* 1969 ''[[Crosby, Stills & Nash (album)|Crosby, Stills & Nash]]'' (CSN)\n* 1970 ''[[D\u00e9j\u00e0 Vu (Crosby, Stills, Nash & Young album)|D\u00e9j\u00e0 Vu]]'' (CSNY) \n* 1971 ''[[4 Way Street]]'' (CSNY)  (live) \n* 1974 ''[[So Far (Crosby, Stills, Nash & Young album)|So Far]]'' (CSNY) \n* 1977 ''[[CSN (album)|CSN]]'' (CSN)\n* 1982 ''[[Daylight Again]]'' (CSN) \n* 1983 ''[[Allies (Crosby, Stills & Nash album)|Allies]]'' (CSN) (live and studio)\n* 1988 ''[[American Dream (Crosby, Stills, Nash & Young album)|American Dream]]'' (CSNY)\n* 1990 ''[[Live It Up (Crosby, Stills & Nash album)|Live It Up]]'' (CSN)\n* 1994 ''[[After the Storm (Crosby, Stills & Nash album)|After the Storm]]'' (CSN)\n* 1999 ''[[Looking Forward]]'' (CSNY) \n* 2008 ''[[D\u00e9j\u00e0 Vu Live]]'' (CSNY) (live)\n\n== Tours ==\n{{Importance section|date=February 2020}}\n{{Prose|section|date=February 2020}}\n\nSee: [[Crosby, Stills, Nash and Young 1969-1970 Tours]]\n\nCrosby, Stills, & Nash have done 29 tours; sometimes with Neil Young. Their first tour was as CSNY, and was a four-leg, 39-date tour that started  on August 16, 1969, at the [[Auditorium Theatre]] in Chicago, with [[Joni Mitchell]] as their opening act. Their second gig was a one-hour show at the [[Woodstock|Woodstock Festival]] in the early morning of August 18, 1969. During that tour they also appeared at the [[Big Sur Folk Festival]] (September 13\u201314, 1969), and the notorious [[Altamont Free Concert]] on December 6, 1969.  The tour ended with three European concerts in January 1970.  They were accompanied on the tour by [[Greg Reeves]] on bass, and [[Dallas Taylor (drummer)|Dallas Taylor]] on drums.\n\nBefore the start of their second tour, Greg Reeves was replaced on bass by Calvin Samuels. The tour is notorious for the tensions within the band, and Dallas Taylor was fired, to be replaced by  [[John Barbata]] on drums, and Stephen Stills was temporarily sacked by the rest of the group. The tour started in Denver Coliseum on 12 May 1970, and finished after 22 dates at the [[Met Center]] in [[Bloomington, Minnesota]] on 9 July 1970, after which the group split up. The double live album ''[[4 Way Street]]'', released April 1971, was recorded at several dates on this tour.\n\n'''[[CSNY 1974|1974 So Far Tour]]'''\n*Bass: [[Tim Drummond]]; Drums: [[Russ Kunkel]]; Percussion: [[Joe Lala]]\n'''[[CSN (album)|1977 CSN Tour]]'''\n*Keyboards: [[Craig Doerge]] (replaced by Kim Bullard); Bass: [[George \"Chocolate\" Perry]]; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]; Percussion: [[Joe Lala]]\n'''[[CSN (album)|1978 Tour]]'''\n*Keyboards: Kim Bullard; Bass: [[George \"Chocolate\" Perry]]; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]; Percussion: [[Joe Lala]]\n'''[[No Nukes: The Muse Concerts for a Non-Nuclear Future|1979 MUSE Concert]]'''\n*Keyboards: [[Craig Doerge]]; Bass: [[Tim Drummond]]; Drums: [[Russ Kunkel]]; Percussion: [[Joe Lala]]\n'''[[Daylight Again|1982 Daylight Again Tour]]'''\n*Guitar: Michael Stergis; Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]] & Michael Hannah (Hannah replaced by [[James Newton Howard]]); Bass: [[George \"Chocolate\" Perry]]; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]; Percussion: Efrain Toro\n'''[[Allies (Crosby, Stills & Nash album)|1983 Allies Tour]]'''\n*Guitar: Michael Stergis; Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]] & Kim Bullard; Bass: [[Kenny Passarelli]]; Drums: Rick Jaeger; Percussion: Efrain Toro\n'''1984 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]] & Kim Bullard; Bass: [[Kenny Passarelli]] (replaced by [[George \"Chocolate\" Perry]]); Drums: [[Ian Wallace (drummer)|Ian Wallace]]; Percussion: [[Joe Lala]]\n'''1985 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]] & Kim Bullard (Bullard replaced by [[Craig Doerge]]); Bass: [[George \"Chocolate\" Perry]]; Drums: Mark T. Williams; Percussion: [[Joe Lala]]\n'''1987 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]]; Bass: [[Bob Glaub]]; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]; Percussion: [[Joe Lala]]\n'''[[American Dream (Crosby, Stills, Nash & Young album)|1988 American Dream Tour]]'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]]; Bass: [[Bob Glaub]]; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]; Percussion: [[Joe Lala]]\n'''1989 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]]; Bass: [[Bob Glaub]]; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]; Percussion: [[Joe Lala]]\n'''[[Live It Up (Crosby, Stills & Nash album)|1990 Live It Up Tour]]'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]] & Kim Bullard; Bass: [[Jorge Calderon]]; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]; Percussion: Michito Sanchez\n'''[[After the Storm (Crosby, Stills & Nash album)|1994 25th Anniversary After the Storm Tour]]'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]]; Bass: Alexis Sklarevski; Drums: [[Jody Cortez]]; Various: [[Ethan Johns]]\n'''1996 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]]; Bass: Gerald Johnson; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''1997 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]]; Bass: Gerald Johnson; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''1999 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]]; Bass: [[James Hutchinson (musician)|James Hutchinson]]; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''[[Looking Forward|2000 CSNY2K Looking Forward Tour]]'''\n*Bass: [[Donald \"Duck\" Dunn|Donald Dunn]]; Drums: [[Jim Keltner]]\n'''2001 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]]; Bass: Gerald Johnson; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''2002 CSNY Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Booker T. Jones]]; Bass: [[Donald \"Duck\" Dunn|Donald Dunn]]; Drums: Steve Potts\n'''2003 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]]; Bass: David Santos; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''[[Greatest Hits (Crosby, Stills & Nash album)|2005 Greatest Hits Tour]]'''\n*Guitar: [[Jeff Pevar]]; Keyboards: [[Mike Finnigan]] & James Raymond; Bass: David Santos; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''[[D\u00e9j\u00e0 Vu Live|2006 CSNY Freedom of Speech Tour]]'''\n*Pedal Steel: [[Ben Keith]]; Keyboards: [[Spooner Oldham]]; Bass: [[Rick Rosas]]; Drums: [[Chad Cromwell]]; Trumpet: Tom Bray\n'''2007 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: James Raymond & Todd Caldwell; Bass: Kevin McCormick; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''2008 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: James Raymond & Todd Caldwell; Bass: Kevin McCormick; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''[[Demos (Crosby, Stills & Nash album)|2009 Demos Tour]]'''\n*Keyboards: James Raymond & Todd Caldwell; Bass: Kevin McCormick; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''2010 Tour'''\n*Keyboards: James Raymond & Todd Caldwell; Bass: Kevin McCormick; Drums: [[Joe Vitale (musician)|Joe Vitale]]\n'''[[CSN 2012|2012 Tour]]'''\n*Guitar: [[Shane Fontayne]]; Keyboards: James Raymond & Todd Caldwell; Bass: Kevin McCormick; Drums: [[Steve DiStanislao]]\n'''2014 Tour'''\n*Guitar: [[Shane Fontayne]]; Keyboards: James Raymond & Todd Caldwell; Bass: Kevin McCormick; Drums: [[Steve DiStanislao]]\n'''2015 Tour'''\n*Guitar: [[Shane Fontayne]]; Keyboards: James Raymond & Todd Caldwell; Bass: Kevin McCormick; Drums: [[Steve DiStanislao]] (replaced by [[Russ Kunkel]])\n\n{{#tag:timeline|\nImageSize = width:800 height:auto barincrement:18\nPlotArea = left:100 bottom:60 top:0 right:15\nAlignbars = justify\nDateFormat  = mm/dd/yyyy\nPeriod = from:01/01/1969 till:01/01/2016\nTimeAxis = orientation:horizontal format:yyyy\n\nColors =\n  id:drums      value:orange       legend:Drums\n  id:bass     value:blue     legend:Bass \n  id:percussion     value:claret   legend:Percussion\n  id:keys    value:purple       legend:Keyboards\n   id:organ      value:skyblue      legend:Organ\n   id:guitar     value:green     legend:Guitar\n   id:steel value:teal   legend:Steel_Guitar\n   id:trumpet   value:pink      legend:Trumpet\n\n  id:Tours          value:gray(0.5)\n  id:bars           value:gray(0.95)\n  id:Lines       value:gray(0.7)      legend:Live_album\n  id:bs value:gray(0.1)\n  id:hh value:gray(0.3)\n\nLegend = orientation:horizontal position:bottom \nScaleMajor = unit:year increment:2 start:1969\nScaleMinor = unit:year increment:1 start:1969\nBackgroundColors =  bars:bars\n\nBarData =\n\n   bar:Taylor    text:\"Dallas Taylor\"\n   bar:Barbata     text:\"Johnny Barbata\"\n   bar:Kunkel text:\"Russ Kunkel\"\n   bar:Vitale    text:\"Joe Vitale\" \n   bar:Jaeger    text: \"Rick Jaeger\"  \n   bar:Wallace    text: \"Ian Wallace\"  \n   bar:Williams   text: \"Mark Williams\"  \n     bar:Cortez    text:\"Jody Cortez\"\n   bar:Keltner   text:\"Jim Keltner\"\n   bar:Potts      text:\"Smokey Potts\"\n   bar:Cromwell    text:\"Chad Cromwell\"\n   bar:DiStanislao   text:\"Steve DiStanislao\"\n\n   bar:Lala     text:\"Joe Lala\"\n   bar:Toro    text:\"Efrain Toro\"\n   bar:Sanchez   text:\"Michito Sanchez\"\n   bar:Johns    text: \"Ethan Johns\"  \n   bar:Doerge   text:\"Craig Doerge\"\n   bar:Bullard      text:\"Kim Bullard\"\n   bar:Finnigan   text:\"Mike Finnigan\"\n   bar:Hannah     text:\"Michael Hannah\"\n   bar:Howard  text:\"James Newton Howard\"\n   bar:Jones    text:\"Booker T. Jones\"\n   bar:Raymond     text:\"James Raymond\"\n   bar:Oldham    text: \"Spooner Oldham\"  \n   bar:Caldwell    text: \"Todd Caldwell\"\n\n   bar:Reeves   text:\"Greg Reeves\"\n  bar:Samuels    text:\"Calvin Samuels\"\n   bar:Drummond   text:\"Tim Drummond\"\n   bar:Perry     text:\"George Perry\"\n\n   bar:Passarelli    text:\"Kenny Passarelli\"\n\n   bar:Glaub    text:\"Bob Glaub\"\n   bar:Calderon      text:\"Jorge Calderon\"\n   bar:Sklarevski   text:\"Alexis Sklarevski\" \n   bar:Johnson   text: \"Gerald Johnson\"  \n   bar:Hutchinson    text:\"Hutch Hutchinson\"\n   bar:Dunn      text:\"Donald Dunn\"\n   bar:Santos 